description.plain:
Olajide “JJ” Olatunji (born 19 June 1993), better known as KSI, is a British YouTube star, rapper, boxer, actor and co-founder of the entertainment collective known as the Sidemen. He was born and raised in Watford, Hertfordshire, England. His main channel, “KSI,” is now his official artist channel. KSI is short for his YouTube channel name KSIOlajideBT, which derives from “KSI” (a Halo clan), also meaning knowledge, strength, and integrity, his name, and “BT,” meaning “British Telecom.”

KSI started doing YouTube in 2010 and has now grown to be one of the most subscribed YouTubers in the world. Apart from being a YouTube sensation, he has also become an artist.

Back in the day when KSI started doing YouTube, he was already making songs in his videos. The first song was his Call of Duty 1v5 Rap. At the time, he had only 50 subscribers.

On 12 April 2019, KSI and Randolph released their collaborative album New Age, the name resembling how they are creating a new style of music, which is portrayed through the different styles of beats used for the tracks. The album features guest appearances from Talia Mar, JME, and Quadeca.

On 22 May 2020, KSI dropped his debut solo album, titled Dissimulation. The album explored JJ’s own inner self and conflict with not just himself, but those around him, something he has said he found difficult exploring. The album features guest appearances from Offset from the hip-hop trio Migos, Smokepurpp, Lil Pump, Swarmz, Tion Wayne, Jeremih, Trippie Redd, Aiyana-Lee, the first official artist signed to his record label “The Online Takeover”, S-X, Lil Baby,  and Rick Ross. Three days later, on 25 May 2020, KSI dropped the deluxe with additional guest appearances from AJ Tracey, Rich the Kid, Randolph, and Crypt.

This song has since been KSI’s most popular song, gathering more than 33 million streams on Spotify and over 100 million views on YouTube.

songs.title: Millions

description.plain:
According to KSI it was the hardest song to make and it took the longest due to his exploration of close personal relationships, the fact that it doesn’t have a feature on a feature heavy album and acts as the closing track, makes its significance immediately obvious.
The first verse is about his family, mainly Deji (his brother) whom he had a public back and forth with.
The second is about his girlfriend, who has been kept away from the public, but has JJ’s appreciation acting as a more heartfelt contrast to the previous verse of conflict.

description.plain:
“Poppin“ is a single that was released March 27, 2020, by rapper, boxer, and YouTube sensation KSI. The song features Smokepurpp and Lil Pump, two rappers both hailing from Florida.

On the track, the three rappers flex their fame and wealth, a common theme in all three artists' tracks. For example, on KSI’s early 2020 track “Wake Up Call,“ he raps:

X amount to exhibit
I’m winnin' in different avenues (‘Nues)
Trippy my revenue (Ayy)
Don’t see me ever lose

The instrumental noticeably samples the melody from “What The Fuck Is Happening,” an early 2020 track by  $uicideboy$.

This is the third single released in preparation for KSI’s debut studio album, Dissimulation. The singles released prior to this are “Down Like That“ and “Wake Up Call.“

“On Point” is a diss track by British YouTuber KSI. The song is aimed at American YouTuber Logan Paul, with the song flaunting his money and flashy lifestyle. KSI used this track as his entrance music when he fought Logan in a Pay-Per-View boxing fight which took place on the 25th of August.

The song’s corresponding music video contains numerous references to Logan and the people around him. The ‘beef’ between the two had escalated prior to this song’s release.

songs.title: Houdini

description.plain:
“Houdini” is an afroswing/afrobashment track released by KSI, featuring fellow UK rap artists Swarmz and Tion Wayne. Houdini appeared on KSI’s debut album Dissimulation, which released May 22, 2020.

The songs title refers to renowned stunt performer/escape artist Harry Houdini. KSI uses Houdini’s name to connect his ability to commit a crime then disappear with Houdini’s ability to escape and vanish from seemingly impossible tasks with ease.

The song was first teased on the April 17, 2020 on KSI’s twitter and was released 7 days later on the April 24, 2020 at midnight on all streaming platforms. The official music video was uploaded to KSI’s main channel later that day.

songs.title: Holiday

description.plain:
KSI’s “Holiday” was released alongside a music video on June 18, 2021 as the fourth single from his upcoming sophomore studio album, All Over the Place.

On this song, KSI showcases his progression in singing, and how every time he’s with his significant other it feels like a holiday and a break from the pressures of the world.

Originally, KSI’s intended to release the song “You” as the fourth single for his album. He stated that the single was changed due to a series of leaks of “You” and his desire to release a song no one had heard before.

KSI spoke about this song for Apple Music:
    “Yet another song inspired by my girlfriend. Whenever we’re together, it feels like I’m on holiday. She helps me relax, calms me down, and makes my life easy—especially when things are getting stressful.”

songs.title: Patience

description.plain:
KSI recruits Polo G and YUNGBLUD for “Patience,” the first collaboration between the three artists. Over an upbeat pop beat, the trio sing about their relationships, past hardships they’ve faced, and how they have changed because of them.

The song’s existence was first confirmed by KSI on January 8th, 2021, during his What’s Good Podcast appearance, hosted by Miniminter and Randolph. During his interview, KSI claimed that it is the best song from his album, and hinted that there was a major artist featured.

KSI officially announced the song with an Instagram post on March 4th, where it was revealed that YUNGBLUD and Polo G were the featured artists.

description.plain:
“Ares” is a response to Youtuber and rapper Quadeca’s song “Insecure”. KSI and Quadeca’s beef started when KSI went on the What’s Good Podcast and called out various Youtube rappers. When co-host Miniminter brought up Quadeca and said he personally liked him and his music, KSI was quick to disagree, saying:

Quadeca, his last track was dead…
I feel like Quadeca thinks he’s sicker than he actually is.

These comments infuriated Quadeca and, in a response video, he said that he was going to make a diss track towards KSI to prove him wrong. Three days later, Quadeca dropped “Insecure.” In KSI’s reaction video, he claimed that the song was good and that he would bite and write a response. Hence, “Ares” was released.

The official music video was released on June 27, 2017, the same day the song was released.
